JENKINS INSTALLATION GUIDE  (Youtube Channel Name : Easytech_9S) {DAY-1}

PRE-REQUISITE

EC2 (AMAZON LINUX t2.medium)
Enable Port Number (Custom TCP =  8080)

Commands :

sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo

sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

sudo yum upgrade

sudo dnf install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel ( JAVA )
 
sudo yum install jenkins

sudo systemctl enable jenkins

sudo systemctl start jenkins

sudo systemctl status jenkins

JENKINS INTEGRATION WITH GITHUB {DAY-2}
Step-1  Install Git in jenkins Sever (Command --> sudo yum install git -y)

Step-2  Jenkins Dashboard >>>>
New Item >> FreeStyle Project >>>> 
Source Code Management >>>>
O Git >>>> Repository URL & Credentials (Give This Info Here) >>>>
Branches to build
(Specify Github repo Branch) >>>> Apply & Save >>>> Build now 

JENKINS INTEGRATION WITH MAVEN {DAY-2}
Step-1 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> Manage Jenkins >>>>
Pulgins >>>> Availabale Pulgins >>>>
Maven Integration plugin (Search & Install) .

Step-2 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> Manage Jenkins >>>> 
Tools >>>> Maven installations (Scroll Down) >>>>
Name & Version (Add) >>>> Apply & Save 

Step-3 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> FreeStyle Project >>>>
Build Steps >>>> Build Steps >>>>
Invoke top-level Maven targets >>>>
Maven Version & Goals (Specify here) >>>> Build now .
 
JENKINS INTEGRATION WITH SONARQUBE SERVER {DAY-2}
Step-1 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> Manage Jenkins >>>> 
Pulgins >>>> Availabale Pulgins >>>>
SonarQube Scanner for Jenkins (Search & Install)

Step-2 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> Manage Jenkins >>>>
Tools >>>> SonarQube Scanner installations >>>> Select versions 

Step-3 Jenkins Dashboard >>>> Manage Jenkins >>>>
System >>>> SonarQube servers >>>>
Environment variables >>>> Name & Server URL & Server authentication token >>>>
(Specify Goal : clean install sonar:sonar) Save & Apply . 

DEVOPS PROJECT-1 WITH JENKINS (DAY-3)

Step-1 : Jenkins Dashboard >>>> New Item >>>> Freestyle Project>>>>

Step-2 : Integrate GitHub by using GitHub Repository Details 

Step-3 : Integrate Maven and give goal as (clean install)

Step-4 : Inetgrate SonarQube and give goal as (clean install sonar:sonar) 

Step-5 : Apply & Save Finally Click on Build Now and Click on Console OutPut .

DEVOPS PROJECT-2 WITH JENKINS ---- {SCRIPTED WAY PIPELINE} (DAY-3)

Step-1 : Jenkins Dahboard >>>> New Item >>>> Pipeline 

Step-2 : Configure >>>> Pipeline >>>> Defination >>>> Pipeline script 

Step-3 : Write a script >>>> apply & save >>>> Build Now 

DEVOPS PROJECT-3 WITH JENKINS ---- {DECLARATIVE WAY PIPELINE} (DAY-3)

Step-1 : Jenkins Dahboard >>>> New Item >>>> Pipeline 

Step-2 : Configure >>>> Pipeline >>>> Defination >>>> Pipeline script 

Step-3 : Write a script >>>> apply & save >>>> Build Now 


